<FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: SARYRN PVP TOURNAMENT - please read</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Don't you think trying to schedule this before you even have the rules worked out a bit premature.  It is a great idea and something I had always thought would be a lot of fun.  I would suggest contacting the gms of various guilds and see what kind of support you can get from them.  Post on the various public boards for each guild.  I am sure there are many OOP, TWC, ToE, GoL, AC, Fam, Isengard, and others I cant think of right now, guild members who would love to do this but the best place to start would be the leaders of those respective guilds to see if they would support it.</font><P><a href="http://www.col.dk/"target="GoL"><img src="http://members.home.net/mike.lawrence2000/Signatures/kynneth_03.jpg" border="0">



<P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#242422><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/utelivaksk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TelivakSK</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#DDA0DD>4/30/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#DDA0DD>9:48:00 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: SARYRN PVP TOURNAMENT - please read</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Hmm, I don't see you stating this in your original post Gran so I'll bring it up.  The cover charge to enter the tourny should be level dependent.  You know, level 20-29 20pp, level 30-39 50pp, 40-49 100pp, 50-60 200pp, etc.  Also, since you have a very stringent level range, it would be a good idea to not put all the collected PPs into one pool and instead, pool them accordingly to the level range.  For example, the contestents in the level 31-33 range give their entrance fee to so_and_so.  The winner of that level range only gets 65% of the PP pool collected by that certain so_and_so.  <br>
<br>
What this would mean is that you'll need one person to collect the entrance fee for each and every level range.  It could be logistic hell, no doubt, but it would be fair at least.  If 8 people show up between 30-33 range and 16 people show up between 34-38, it wouldn't be fair to the winner of the 34-38 range winner if the PP he won is the same amount as the 30-33 winner.  Afterall, the 34-38 winner did have to fight thru twice as many people to win his level range when compared to the 30-33 winner.<br>
<br>
It might also be a good idea to divide the contestents down further besides the level range breakdown.  You know, pit the casters against the casters and meleers against the meleers.  I doubt a warrior/monk/rogue would stand much of a change against a wizzy unless he's got 150+ MR/FR/CR, especially at higher levels.  Lastly, you'll need a policy on twinks.  Like it or not, twinks have a better chance of winning these tourneys than non-twinks.  A level 30 war in full Crafted, Wurmslayer, Yak and FBSS is gonna kick the crap out of a level 30 that is still dressed in bronze and armed with a BIBS.  Either make it a twink only tourney or just ban them completely.  <br>
<br>
Welp, these are just a couple of ideas tossed around, up to you to decide if they're good or not heh. </font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/uandvarishadowmist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AndvariShadowmist</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Bastard Bard</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#DDA0DD>4/30/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#DDA0DD>11:14:26 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: SARYRN PVP TOURNAMENT - please read</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Telivak,<br>
